    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Email_InsertCustomEmailAttachment",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to insert a new record into the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scheduler.DistributionJobEmailAttachment",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. This record represents an email attachment associated with a specific distribution job. The procedure takes in parameters for the attachment content, the job sequence ID, the size of the attachment in bytes, and the filename of the attachment. It then inserts these values into the table along with timestamps for when the record was added and last updated."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "INSERT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " operation into a database table. It does not include any complex logic, conditional statements, or error handling, which keeps its complexity low."
        }
      ]
    },
